<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Tribune" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Tribune,</orth> an officer of ancient Rome, chosen by the plebeians to defend their liberties against the nobility: <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.219" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 219</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.9.6" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 9, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.2.155" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 155</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 21</bibl>. 31 etc. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 46</bibl> 181 etc. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.7.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 7, 8</bibl>. Invested with the office of judges: <bibl n="shak. cor 2.1.77" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 1, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.23" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 23</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>